**Here are the core personas/roles to design for:**

Creator/Owner (Fractionalizer)
Goals: Fractionalize their NFT, set terms (symbol, policy, max supply), mint/receive shares, list shares.
Key actions: Setup custody, select NFT, configure vault, fractionalize, create listings.
UX needs: Clear custody explanation, step-by-step wizard, simple validation, success receipts.

Investor (Buyer/Holder)
Goals: Discover vaults, assess value, buy shares, monitor holdings, claim distributions.
Key actions: Browse vaults, view metadata and activity, buy via listings, track balances, claim payouts.
UX needs: Trust signals (creator, events, supply), price/TVL, recent activity, easy purchase/claim flows.

Trader (Secondary-market participant)
Goals: List shares, cancel/fill orders, track open orders.
Key actions: Create/cancel/fill listings, view order status/history.
UX needs: Fast listing form, clear fees/quotes, order status feedback.

Admin (Platform operator)
Goals: Initialize platform resources, attest vaults, mint shares (policy-driven), manage settings, schedule distributions.
Key actions: Setup admin, create vault metadata (attest), mint shares, set transfer mode, schedule distributions, finalize buyouts (interim).
UX needs: Admin dashboard, guardrails, audit trails.

Governance Participant (Future holder voting)
Goals: Propose/vote on buyouts or policies.
Key actions: Review proposals, cast votes, see results.
UX needs: Voting power visibility, quorum/support thresholds, deadlines.

Liquidity Provider (Future AMM/pools)
Goals: Provide liquidity, earn fees, assess pool health.
Key actions: Create pool, add/remove liquidity, swap.
UX needs: Reserve/fee visuals, risk disclosures.

Integrator/Analyst (API/Index consumer)
Goals: Consume indexed data, build analytics/tools.
Key actions: Query GraphQL, read metrics.
UX needs: Stable API, schema docs, example queries.
